<div class="container mt-4">

    <div class="card shadow-sm p-4">

        <h2 class="mb-3">Privacy & Data Handling</h2>

        <p>
            TechMove Logistics is designed as an enterprise-style logistics management system that handles
            client, contract, and service request data in a structured and secure manner.
        </p>

        <p>
            All data processed within this application is intended for demonstration purposes as part of the
            PROG7311 academic module. The system simulates real-world logistics workflows, including
            contract management, service request processing, and secure document handling.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <h5>Data Security Principles</h5>

        <ul>
            <li>Client and contract data is stored in a structured relational database using Entity Framework Core</li>
            <li>Authentication is handled using secure token-based mechanisms (JWT)</li>
            <li>File uploads are managed through controlled storage mechanisms (local or external storage services)</li>
            <li>The system follows separation of concerns between API, Client, and Data layers</li>
        </ul>

        <hr />

        <h5>External Integrations</h5>

        <p>
            The system may interact with external services such as Supabase (for file storage) and currency
            conversion APIs to simulate real-world distributed system behaviour.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <h5>Academic Context</h5>

        <p>
            This application was developed as part of the Programming 7311 module to demonstrate
            enterprise software architecture principles, including:
        </p>

        <ul>
            <li>Layered architecture design</li>
            <li>Design patterns (Factory, Strategy, Observer)</li>
            <li>Containerised deployment using Docker</li>
            <li>Automated testing and CI/CD pipelines</li>
        </ul>

